[SN]TITLE[SN]
'Serious' collision closes A90 carriageway north of Dundee

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A "serious" road traffic collision has closed the southbound carriageway of the A90 north of Dundee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the scene at Powrie at about 15:30 on Monday.
It is understood the collision involved a car and a lorry.
Traffic Scotland described the incident as "serious" and said local diversions were in place for small vehicles, with lorries currently being stacked at Tealing.
